	abstract = {In this paper, we propose a modified bi-inertial viscosity forward-backward splitting algorithms by integrating the viscosity approximation method with an inertial term to solve monotone inclusion problems. Strong convergence theorems are established under suitable conditions within the framework of Hilbert spaces. The proposed algorithms are applied to compute minimum-norm least-squares solutions of unconstrained linear systems. To demonstrate the effectiveness of our methods, we implement them in the Extreme Learning Machine (ELM) framework for breast cancer classification. Numerical experiments show that the Lasso-based variant achieves the highest accuracy in the 5-fold cross-validation setting, while the Tikhonov-based variant outperforms all others in the 10-fold setting. Overall, the Tikhonov-based algorithm exhibits the best generalization performance across both strategies, confirming the robustness and practical applicability of the proposed methods for real-world medical data analysis. © 2026 Elsevier B.V.},
